If I could give 4.5 stars I would, but since I can only do whole stars, I have to give Rosetta a 4. I have visited the Miami location a few times and I am usually pleased by my experiences with minor exceptions. There are definitely some hits and misses on the menu, which is why I can't give Rosetta a 5 star rating. I enjoy their flatbreads, ciabatta breads, and sandwiches for the most part with some needing a hint more flavor than others. Same issue goes for their desserts. This visit we ordered a chocolate brownie, but it missed the mark by being very dry and overly rich. I have enjoyed my coffees at Rosetta with no complaint. Caution to your pocket book because Rosetta might seem like a quick grab and go stop to eat, but their prices can be quiet high depending on what you order. I would still recommend Rosetta, and clearly I enjoy it because I have been a returning customer. The location at Aventura Mall is stellar, located next to restrooms, and next to the Apple store.

First let me say the pastries look amazing, the presentation of all their food is beautiful! and the place is spotless- The young lady behind the counter quickly came over to assist me.. I asked, pointing to the almond pastry and asked for additional description. I asked if it was made with marzipan and a moist cake. She nodded her head and said yes in very broken English. I asked how much it was and she said $6.00. So I asked for it to stay in a plate. The cashier Massimo was very helpful I asked about the mini pastries by the register and he suggested the mini custard bigne. Which i had to also try.. he rang me up to find out the almond cake was $9.00 not $6.00. Wow! I didn't say anything I thought if it was as described it was worth it and I could take most of it home. I sat down and there were no forks or knives to cut the cake. As it turns out the Almond Cake is not a cake at all.. it is a hard crumbling tasteless cookie.. with no hint of marzipan. A big $9.00 fail! Really! It turns out the young lady doesn't speak English! She had no idea what I was saying! Really! The custard bigne was absolutely delicious! Of course I ordered the mini one! $9.00 for a tasteless cookie is unfortunately a big mistake on my part. I was treating myself . I work 3 jobs so this really hurt. I left the almond cookie/cake right on the counter and walked out. Truly if a customer is asking something very specific about a food item please bring someone over who understands.. not everyone has money to throw away..

Rosetta Bakery is yet another food addition in Aventura Mall's expanded wing but this is actually located indoors across from Macy's entrance.  I stopped here to grab a sandwich but ended up having one of the veggie pizzas, mushroom and spinach. It was just calling my name lol :)  It's not the best pizza I've ever had but the ingredients were definitely fresh. Plus they're not stingy with the toppings here. I also enjoyed eating my pizza at their gorgeous seating area in the middle of the hall. (See my pics).  Like the original Collins Avenue location, they also have focaccia sandwiches and a variety of desserts on display. They all look enticing but be prepared to pay a premium. Just remember, you are paying for high-quality food so this is not your average bakery. Next time, I will try the fruit tart because it just looks divine.
